  "body": "I've created a new account with a display name `Test Account 7`.\r\nNotice that `T` and `A` are capital letters. This happens automatically when entering a display name during onboarding (as if the UI doesn't allow for lower case display names).\r\n\r\nHowever, once set up, the name is in fact rendered in lower cases letters only in various places:\r\n\r\nHere's the profile view:\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-04-04 17-06-53](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/161574025-74edd579-b81b-4f58-a51f-7833342cb3b5.png)\r\n\r\nHere's profile popup:\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-04-04 17-07-21](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/161574109-0829b575-eaef-4b9f-97d6-c87227d3ffad.png)\r\n\r\nI think the onboarding process should either allow me to use lower case letters, or at least render the display name exactly how it was entered. Not sure in which scenario we would not want this to be true.\r\n\r\n",
